by authors: the uncertainty in cross sections is less
than 15% and have been confirmed by at least two, and
in some cases three or more, independent measurements.
Estimated uncertainties less than 15%.
several targets were irradiated with deuteron beam
with 21.5 MeV primary energy. Each target stack was
subjected to an irradiation of approximately 4500
micro-coulomb. The activation cross section was
determined by comparison beta counting.
three monitor foils were placed into each stack. An
aluminum and a bismuth foil at the front of the stack
and a bismuth foil at the rear of the stack.
target cooling was achieved by stacking the targets 8mm
apart and forcing air trough these spaces.
different elemental and compound targets with natural
isotopic composition with an average thickness less
than 5 mg/cm2. Some target material were available only
in powder form. From these materials 3-5 mg/cm2 thick
targets were prepared by sedimentation method.
data were taken from tables 1-5 of Phys. Rev.
